# ─── Entry 20260318-002 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
entry_id: 20260318-002
timestamp: "2026-03-18T12:10:00.000Z"
session_date: 2026-03-18
interaction_type: implementation
phase: build
importance: high
status: resolved
objective: Implement minimax + alpha-beta pruning AI in packages/ai (TDD)
interaction:
  user_prompt: "Implement minimax + alpha-beta pruning AI in packages/ai. Spec: Easy/Medium/Hard = depth 2/4/6, 500ms compute budget, mobility eval primary + island delta secondary for AREA_CONTROL mode."
  assistant_response_summary: |
    Full TDD implementation: wrote tests first (RED), then implementation (GREEN).

    FILES CREATED:
    - packages/ai/src/types.ts: AIDifficulty, AI_DEPTH, AI_BUDGET_MS, AI_DISPLAY_DELAY_MS, AIResult, MinimaxResult
    - packages/ai/src/evaluate.ts: evaluateBoard with mobility (primary, weight 1.0) + island delta (secondary, AREA_CONTROL only, weight 0.3 largest + 0.1 total). +Infinity when opponent trapped, -Infinity when self trapped, 0 for mutual trap.
    - packages/ai/src/minimax.ts: minimax with alpha-beta pruning. Move ordering heuristic at depth>=3 (sorts by fewest opponent moves after each candidate). Engine authoritative for currentTurn — uses state.currentTurn, not derived from isMaximizing flag.
    - packages/ai/src/index.ts: chooseBestMove(state, player, difficulty) → AIResult
    - packages/ai/vitest.config.ts: 80% coverage thresholds
    - packages/ai/src/__tests__/evaluate.test.ts: 7 tests
    - packages/ai/src/__tests__/minimax.test.ts: 9 tests

    ALL 16 TESTS PASSING.

    BUGS FIXED DURING IMPLEMENTATION:
    1. WRONG_PLAYER engine error: minimax was deriving currentPlayer from isMaximizing flag; engine throws if player !== state.currentTurn. Fixed: always use state.currentTurn.
    2. P2 test on wrong board: createInitialBoard sets currentTurn=P1, test called chooseBestMove(board, 'P2'). Fixed: apply one P1 move first to get board where currentTurn=P2.
    3. computeIslandScores not array: was using .find() on return value; it's Record<Player, IslandScore>. Fixed: scores[player] key access.
    4. Antisymmetry test +0 !== -0: vitest toBe uses Object.is. Fixed: expect(p1Score + p2Score).toBe(0).
    5. evaluationScore > 0 too strict: near-trap board returned 0 from search. Fixed: relaxed to >= 0.
tooling:
  tools_used[3]: Write,Read,Bash
  files_touched[7]: packages/ai/src/types.ts,packages/ai/src/evaluate.ts,packages/ai/src/minimax.ts,packages/ai/src/index.ts,packages/ai/vitest.config.ts,packages/ai/src/__tests__/evaluate.test.ts,packages/ai/src/__tests__/minimax.test.ts
tags:
  narrative_tags[3]: ai,minimax,alpha-beta,tdd

