  assistant_response_summary: |
    Created supabase/migrations/001_initial_schema.sql:
    - players table (id=Clerk user ID, username, avatar_url)
    - game_sessions table (mode, p1_id, p2_id, winner_id, move_count, duration_seconds)
    - player_stats table (player_id, mode) with primary key composite — denormalized W/L/D
    - RLS enabled: players/stats readable by self, game_sessions by participants
    - increment_player_stats() RPC for atomic upsert+increment (avoids race conditions)
    - updated_at trigger on players

    Created apps/server/src/db.ts:
    - createClient with service role key (bypasses RLS)
    - upsertPlayer(PlayerRow) — called on socket auth in Phase 5
    - saveGameSession(input) — inserts game_sessions row, calls increment_player_stats for both players
    - getPlayerStats(playerId) — returns {SUDDEN_DEATH, AREA_CONTROL} W/L/D or null

    Modified apps/server/src/session.ts:
    - Added startedAt: number to GameSession (for duration_seconds calculation)
    - Added playerIds: Record<Player, string> | null to GameSession (null until Phase 5 Clerk auth)

    Modified apps/server/src/socket.ts:
    - Added persistGame() helper — fire-and-forget, only runs when playerIds is set
    - Wired into all 3 GAME_OVER locations: timeout, normal game end, resign

    Committed as bdb9a82.
