# ─── Entry 20260318-007 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
entry_id: 20260318-007
timestamp: "2026-03-18T13:45:00.000Z"
session_date: 2026-03-18
interaction_type: implementation
phase: build
importance: high
status: resolved
objective: Phase 5 - Clerk auth integration (app + server)
interaction:
  user_prompt: "Install Clerk, add ClerkProvider to app, JWT on socket handshake, server auth middleware"
  assistant_response_summary: |
    Installed: @clerk/clerk-expo + expo-secure-store (app), @clerk/backend (server).

    apps/app/stores/authStore.ts (new):
    - Zustand store: token, userId, username, setToken, setUser, clear

    apps/app/app/_layout.tsx (rewritten):
    - Wrapped in ClerkProvider with tokenCache (SecureStore on device, memory fallback on web)
    - AuthSync component: syncs Clerk session into authStore on sign-in/out
    - CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY from expo-constants extra or EXPO_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY env

    apps/app/hooks/useSocket.ts (rewritten):
    - Reads token from authStore
    - Passes token in socket.io handshake auth: { token }
    - Reconnect config: 10 attempts, 2s delay, 8s max (handles Fly.io cold wake ~3-5s)
    - Re-creates socket when token changes (sign in/out)
    - SERVER_URL updated: dev=localhost:3001, prod=cavatrapi-server.fly.dev

    apps/server/src/auth.ts (new):
    - verifySocketToken(token) using @clerk/backend verifyToken (standalone fn, not method)
    - Fetches display name from Clerk users.getUser after verification
    - Fails open: returns null for guests, expired tokens, or unconfigured keys

    apps/server/src/index.ts:
    - Socket connection handler is now async
    - Calls verifySocketToken(token) from handshake auth before registerSocketHandlers

    apps/server/src/socket.ts:
    - registerSocketHandlers now accepts VerifiedUser | null
    - Module-level socketUsers Map (socketId → VerifiedUser) for cross-socket lookup at match time
    - On connection: upsertPlayer fire-and-forget if authenticated
    - On JOIN_GAME: populates session.playerIds when both sockets have verified users
    - On disconnect: cleans up socketUsers entry

    apps/server/src/session.ts:
    - Added startedAt: number to GameSession
    - Added playerIds: Record<Player, string> | null to GameSession

    Committed as 479e572. Both server and app typecheck clean.
tooling:
  tools_used[3]: Write,Edit,Bash
  files_touched[7]: apps/app/stores/authStore.ts,apps/app/app/_layout.tsx,apps/app/hooks/useSocket.ts,apps/server/src/auth.ts,apps/server/src/index.ts,apps/server/src/socket.ts,apps/server/src/session.ts
tags:
  narrative_tags[3]: clerk,auth,jwt

